         <abstract>
            <p>The paper treats, in a particularly simple fashion, the practical problem of the rate of convergence of discretization in real and complex Chebyshev approximation. Both linear and nonlinear approximations are discussed and, subject to certain conditions, quadratic convergence of the discretizations is obtained along with an explicit rate constant which can be estimated numerically.</p>
          </abstract>
